Sven-Ingvars started as a pop/rock group back in 1956. They had a career peak in
the 60s with a lot of entries on the Swedish top chart "Svensktoppen". They are
the second best group/artist on this chart with 54 entries. After some less
successful years in the late 70s and early 80s they had a revival in the 90s.
They played at the Hultsfred festival 1991. The singer Sven-Erik Magnusson (only
original member today) said (not exactly quoted): We have now been in the music
business for so long that we can tour, making covers of our own early hits. <a href="
